2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses machine learning algorithms for rs-fMRI based clinical or behavioral prediction.
3. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a neural network framework for analyzing rs-fMRI data.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses artificial intelligence techniques for analyzing rs-fMRI data.
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper discusses the potential of rs-fMRI scans as a diagnostic or prognostic tool for a wide variety of conditions, which is relevant to the field of human-computer interaction.
